										<li id="comment-122988" class="commentbody"><div class="commenthead"><img alt='Reuel`s avatar' src='http://trilema.com/default_avatar.png' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />								<div class="commentcount">12</div>
								<span class="authorlink">Reuel</span>&nbsp;								<span class=""></span>
													<br />
								<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-122988" title="">Friday, 22 September 2017</a>
							</div>
						<p>To the indolent commenter's dismay, but honestly not to his surprise, the modern aristocrat was not in the very least pleased with his witty remark. "Darn... I kind of botched it. At least he got some SEO out of it..." the old youngin thought to himself. And then: "Bah. These middle class virtues, past a certain age they are just so ingrained, it's hard to switch to more elevated mannerisms. This eagerness to please, like my tendency to pity, this forgiveness, aversion of conflict, I've been taught erroneous virtues all my life. I even forgave him for posting pr0n without NSFW tags, a feat which cost me my cushy job at the code cube. Modern society has even robbed me of the capability to be a proper enemy!"<br />
And so, he gave himself an excuse for lingering, loitering. Letting all manners of ideas entice him, while letting go unnoticed truths way more terrifying for quite a while. But one night, it struck him that the virtues, formerly thought to be learned behavior, might be pretty much hardcoded in his lineage. The prefered mannerisms might be, for the same reason, strictly unnattainable, or statistically very unlikely to be attained. They might even not be prefered for him at all. It even might very well be a case of just not the right physicality to uphold them. Sadness came over him, but uncharacteristically, it also spurred him into action. Suddenly, he found himself typing, the words seemed to force themselves out of him.<br />
"Could you think of a worse fate, than to be able to at least recognize things like genius and true nobility, or understand why these are amongst the highest of things, and to understand that almost no one understands, but not be able to partake! To understand how every other soul must react to and sings praise to the exceptional, even though singing praise for the great part constitutes outright hatred and scorn, or just bad jokes and downplaying, in the more subtly wretched types. That it is infinitely better to be the action, than the reaction!<br />
And if one then knows this to be one's fate, it means to know of one's own wretchedness! How could one endure this knowledge? People don't keep their personal wretchednesses visible for long, at least not in their own sight! They who do get sick. So why don't I feel sick? Why do I feel great, in light of the fact that slavery and running from it, outsideness, too-lateness, must be my lot? Why is my head buzzing! Ah, but yes! It is because..."<br />
A soft hand on his shoulder snapped him out of it, for the most part. Some of the buzz remained.<br />
"Time to get off the pc darling, you've been on fourchannel all evening."<br />
"Only a female could brush away so much profoundness with one stroke", he thought, and he realized that that was a great reason to love her. "I probably should just have said I liked the article."</p>
						</li>

